<subsection xml:id="subsec-area-of-a-triangle">
    <title>Area of a triangle</title>
    <definition xml:id="def-Triangle">
        <statement>
            <p>
                Have you ever seen a triangular 
                field or a slice of bread cut into a triangle?
            </p>
            <p>
                Triangles are shapes with three sides and three corners. we are going to learn how to find the amount of space inside a 
                triangle â€” this is called its area.
            </p>
            <p>
                <m>\textbf{Deriving the Formula (with illustration)}</m>
            </p>
        </statement>
    </definition>
    
    <activity>
        <p>
            <m>\textbf{Work in groups}</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        
                        Draw a rectangle on the board (e.g <m>6 \, \text{cm long}\,4 \, \text{cm tall}</m>) 
                        as shown below.
                        
                    </p>
                    <image width="50%">
                        <latex-image label="tri">
                            
                            \begin{tikzpicture}[scale=1,blue]
                                % Draw rectangle
                                \draw[very thick,] (0,0) rectangle (6,4);
                            
                                % Label base and height
                                \draw[very thick,&lt;-&gt;] (0,-0.5) -- node[below]{Base = 6 cm} (6,-0.5);
                                \draw[very thick,&lt;-&gt;] (-0.5,0) -- node[left]{Height = 4 cm} (-0.5,4);
                            
                            
                            
                                % Label vertices
                                \node at (0,0) [below left] {A};
                                \node at (6,0) [below right] {B};
                                \node at (6,4) [above right] {C};
                                \node at (0,4) [above left] {D};
                            \end{tikzpicture}
                            
                        </latex-image>
                
                            
                     </image>
                    
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        What is the area of the rectangle you have drawn in the board?
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Divide it into two equal triangles by drawing a diagonal line as shown.
                    </p>
                    <image width="50%">
                    <latex-image label="tri1">
                        \begin{tikzpicture}[scale=1]
                            % Draw rectangle
                            \draw[very thick,fill=cyan] (0,0) rectangle (6,4);
                        
                            % Label base and height
                            \draw[very thick,&lt;-&gt;] (0,-0.5) -- node[below]{Base = 6 cm} (6,-0.5);
                            \draw[very thick,&lt;-&gt;] (-0.5,0) -- node[left]{ Height = 4 cm} (-0.5,4);
                        
                            % Draw diagonal line to divide into triangles
                            \draw[dashed, thick, red] (0,0) -- (6,4);
                        
                            % Label vertices
                            \node at (0,0) [below left] {A};
                            \node at (6,0) [below right] {B};
                            \node at (6,4) [above right] {C};
                            \node at (0,4) [above left] {D};
                        \end{tikzpicture}
                    </latex-image>
                        
                    </image>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Divide the area of the rectangle.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        How many triangles did you get from one rectangle?
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Find the area of one triangle.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        What do you notice from the area of the rectangle divided by two and the area of one triangle?
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Share your work with other learners.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
        


        
    </activity>
    <p>
        <m>\textbf{Key Takeaway}</m>
    </p>
    <p>
        A triangle is half of a rectangle.
    </p>
    <p>
        The area of a triangle is given by;
    </p>
    <p>
        <m>\text{Area of triangle}=\frac{1}{2} \times \text{base} \times \text{height}</m>
    </p>
    <p>
        <m>\textbf{Note;}</m>
    </p>
    <p>
        Always make sure the height is at <m>90^\circ</m> to the base!
    </p>
    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Ama wants to paint a triangular 
                wall with a base of <m>8\,m</m> and a height of <m>5\,m</m>. How much space will she paint?
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                <m>\text{The height}=5\,\text{m}</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                <m>\text{The base}=8\,\text{m}</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                Therefore,
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow> \text{A}=\amp \frac{1}{2} \times \text{b} \times \text{h} </mrow>
                    <mrow>= \amp \frac{1}{2} \times 8 \times 5</mrow>
                    <mrow> =\amp \text{1}{2} \times 40 </mrow>
                    <mrow> =\amp 20 \, \text{m}^2 </mrow>
                </md>
                
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Calculate the area of the triangles:
            </p>
            <image>
            <latex-image>
                
                \begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.8]

                    % Triangle 1
                    \draw[very thick] (0,0) -- (6,0) -- (6,5) -- cycle;
                    \node at (3,0.3) {6 cm};
                    \node at (6.7,2.5) {5 cm};
                    \node at (1.2,2.5) {1)};
                    
                    
                    
                    % Triangle 3
                    \begin{scope}[yshift=-5cm]
                    \draw [very thick](0,0) -- (9,0) -- (4.5,4.5) -- cycle;
                    \draw[very thick,dashed] (4.5,4.5) -- (4.5,0);
                    \node at (4.5,-0.4) {9 m};
                    \node at (5,2.2) {10 m};
                    
                    \node at (-0.5,2.5) {3)};
                    
                    \end{scope}
                    
                    % Triangle 2
                    \begin{scope}[xshift=8cm,yshift=-5cm]
                    \draw[very thick] (0,3) -- (10,3) -- (0,8) -- cycle;
                    \node at (0.7,5) {5 km};
                    \node [below]at (4.5,3) {13 km};
                    \node [very thick,black]at (-1,5.5) {2)};
                    \end{scope}
                \end{tikzpicture}
            </latex-image>
                
            </image>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                <m>\text{Area}=\frac{1}{2} b h</m> where <m>b= \text{base of the triangle}  \, \text{and} \,  h= \text{height of the triangle}</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                <ol marker="1)">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Triangle 1
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <md>
                                <mrow> \text{A}=\amp \frac{1}{2} \times 6 \times 5 </mrow>
                                <mrow> =\amp \frac{1}{2} \times 30</mrow>
                                <mrow> =\amp 15 \,cm^2 </mrow>
                            </md>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Triangle 2
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <md>
                                <mrow> \text{A}=\amp \frac{1}{2} \times 13 \times 5 </mrow>
                                <mrow> =\amp \frac{1}{2} \times 65</mrow>
                                <mrow> =\amp 32.5 \,km^2 </mrow>
                            </md>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Triangle 3
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <md>
                                <mrow> \text{A}=\amp \frac{1}{2} \times 9 \times 10 </mrow>
                                <mrow> =\amp \frac{1}{2}\times 90</mrow>
                                <mrow> =\amp 45 \,m^2 </mrow>
                            </md>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Determine the area of a triangle below.
            </p>
            <image width="50%">
            <latex-image label="tri2">
                \begin{tikzpicture}
                    % Draw the right-angled triangle
                    \draw [thick] (0,0) -- (4,0) -- (0,3) -- cycle;
                
                
                    % Side labels
                    \node[left] at (-0.2,1.5) {\Large 15 mm};
                    \node[below] at (2,-0.3) {\Large 20 mm};
                
                
                    % Right-angle marker at P
                    \draw (0,0) -- (0.3,0) -- (0.3,0.3) -- (0,0.3) -- cycle;
                \end{tikzpicture}
            </latex-image>
                
            </image>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                The above figure,
            </p>
            <p>
                <m>\text{the base} = 20\,\text{mm}</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                <m>\text{the heigh}t = 15\,\text{mm}</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                Therefore,
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow>\text{A}= \amp \frac{1}{2} \times b h </mrow>
                    <mrow> =\amp \frac{1}{2} \times 20 \times 15</mrow>
                    <mrow> =\amp \frac{1}{2} \times 300</mrow>
                    <mrow> =\amp 150\, \text{mm}^2 </mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>


    
    
